{
  "stem": "9168.6",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no way for any private citizen, German or any nationality, to get out of Europe for, for the US.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because every passage on every ship and plane had already been booked.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So eventually-- I went on waiting lists.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And eventually, I was able to get a cancellation-- and I'm sure it was out of Bremerhaven-- by ship.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because I know I came home on the SS United States.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it had to be in late May, 1948.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before that, Gary, this particular ship [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] had a great many Jewish refugees in the hold, or the bottom deck.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were ref-- political refugees.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were refugees from, especially, for example, Czechoslovakia, going to the United States.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I can remember that they did not have their kosher food.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they weren't eating.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that came to the attention of the ship's captain so that he could remedy that by providing-- and I'm not that familiar with the diet, you know, for the, the Orthodox Jew.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But he managed to work with the Jewish people on that ship so that he could provide food for them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a long trip-- 12 days, I think.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It may have been more than 12 days, but at least that I know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when, when we came into New York Harbor, [CRYING] and all of the Jews were on deck, [PAUSES FOR 11 SECONDS] at the sight of the Statue of Liberty, they all fell on their knees, sobbing.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[CRYING] And I was right with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] That scene, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] too, was one of the most important scenes that maybe has affected my life after that, and made me so Jewish aware.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
